


Calling
stream_put_error,
estream_put_warning,
estream_put_note,
estream_alert, 
estream_warn, and
estream_note,

            Functions from which

                -   estream_put_error,
                -   estream_put_note, 
                -   estream_put_warning,
                -   estream_alert,
                -   estream_warn, or
                -   estream_note;
            
            "The Functions;" are called should contain the
            statement-like macro reference

                    TRACER_DECLARE ;
         
            in the outermost block scope of the function
            from which any of The Functions are to be
            called. If possible, the declaration should be
            placed ahead of any statement, among the initial
            declarations and initializers. Within the same
            block, one of The Functions may be called as,
            for example,

                    estream_note ( TRACER , "message" ) ;
          
            where message is the text to be displayed in the
            message generated by The Function.
              See also source code for c files with the
            prefix "istream_" in the file name.
